Package etomica.data

Class DataSet

  • java.lang.Object
    • etomica.data.DataSet
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    DataSinkTable

    public class DataSet
extends java.lang.Object
    Receives and organizes data from multiple streams. Fires event when new data arrives; can be configured to fire when any piece of data changes, or to perform action only when all data has changed.

    • Nested Class Summary

      Nested Classes 
      Modifier and Type Class Description
      protected static class  DataSet.DataSetSink
      A special DataSink used by the DataSet to receive Data and DataInfo from a single stream.

      • setUpdatingOnAnyChange

        public void setUpdatingOnAnyChange​(boolean updatingWithAnyChange)
        Describes protocol for firing table events that notify of column data changes. If true, event is fired when any column notifies that it has changed; if false, event is fired only when all columns have notified that they have changed (since last time event was fired).
